Olney High School Yearbook/Journalism Program
April 2 at 8:33 AM Â·

While there may be a hold on all spring academic and athletic competitions at Olney ISD and schools around the state, it is the intent of the Olney High School yearbook staff to put out as complete a yearbook as possible. To make that happen in these strange, quarantined times, we are going to need some help compiling photos of different events. At this time, we are asking the public for the following photos:

1) Softball action shots
2) Baseball action shots
3) OHS track action photos
4) OJH track action photos
5) Homeschool photos or "selfies" (Olney ISD students of all ages)

Email photos you wouldn't mind seeing in the yearbook to mkimbro@olneyisd.net.

Senior parents, we are also still accepting senior ads! Email mkimbro@olneyisd.net for information on how to reserve space to honor your senior in the 2019-2020 yearbook.

ğŸ€ğŸ€ğŸ€ OJH Tournament has finally wrapped up and we have some thanks we would like to give:

1. Mrs. Julie Hinson and Mrs. Shannon Rodriguez for organizing an amazing hospitality room!
2. Our four awesome refs that did a total of 22 games today!
3. All the schools that brought their teams to our first tournament.
4. Mrs. Carla Scrogum for working the gate all day and Mr. Darrell Hudson for all of his hard work!
5. All of our HS Basketball girls for working the table, book, and gate!
6. Lastly, all the parents that allow us to coach their kiddos and cheer us on!

post_text:
Hello to all the Olney Cub Parents, Faculty Members, and Loyal Fans,

The Olney 2020 Baseball Team is hosting a Fungo Golf Tournament Sunday the 17th @1 at the Olney baseball fields. What is Fungo Golf you ask? Well it's just like golf but instead of using golf balls and golf clubs, you use a baseball and baseball bat. I have attached a flyer, course layout, and a score card. We will have warm food, hot and cold drinks, and prizes. So come out Nov. 17th support your Olney Cubs baseball team and most importantly have fun. Hope to see y'all out there. GO CUBS!!!
